On the one hand, technology has made life significantly easier and more efficient. This is because digital tools, ranging from smartphone applications to artificial intelligence systems, enable people to complete tasks more quickly and conveniently. For example, students can use AI tools to solve basic problems or debug simple errors, which saves time and improves productivity. As a result, they can focus more on complex and meaningful tasks. Therefore, technology plays a crucial role in improving daily efficiency.
However, technology has also made people's lives more complicated. This is because people are constantly exposed to notifications and social media, which can be highly distracting. For example, many individuals spend several hours scrolling through their phones instead of focusing on work or study. As a result, this can reduce productivity and increase stress levels. Therefore, technology can sometimes have negative effects on daily life.

